courses offered by alfred m spormann alfred m spormann laboratory home members members of the spormann lab teaching courses offered by alfred m spormann publications spormann lab pubs contact contacting the spormann lab courses offered by alfred m spormann professor spormann teaches a one year curriculum in environmental microbiology the core is composed of two lecture courses cee274a bio280a chemeng 174 environmental microbiology cee274b bio280b chemeng 456 metabolic biochemistry of microorganisms as well as an intensive summer course with a laboratory and computational component cee274s hopkins microbiology course these courses focus on fundamental aspects of bacterial metabolism and physiology molecular microbiology and genomics and molecular evolution the courses are designed for graduate students and advanced undergraduate students with an interest in the molecular basis of the diversity and plasticity of microbes in alternate years professor spormann offers a course on microbial biofilms 0 february 06 2009 lab links research strain database group meeting bioinformatic tools protocols clark network user login login with your sunetid username password create new account request new password
